<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-02-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-02-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="889" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d889">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/1208.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Mexico City</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-02-28">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 28, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Department’s No. 46, February 27, 2 p.m. I think the Department
                            misinterpreted De la Barra’s telegram owing to its involved statement.
                            It was not intended to be definite and conclusive but simply an
                            expression of the good will with which he has taken up his task.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>